          </choice>rāja-śrī-pravarase<pb break="no" n="2v"/><lb break="no" n="7"/><choice>
            <sic>t</sic>
            <corr>n</corr>
          </choice>asya vacanā<unclear>T|</unclear><!-- 
In l2 Mirashi prints naimalyā° (emending to nairmalyā°) in both his editions; the correct reading is naimmalyā°. 
--><!-- 
L4. Mirashi says the visarga of bhagavataḥ is superfluous; since the space is between the visarga and the ś, I prefer to delete the ś. 
--><!-- 
In l5, Mirashi emends the upadhmānīya to an anusvāra; I prefer to emend to m (since that would have been joined to the next letter like an upadhmānīya). I should also note that this bit is very unclear in the rubbing; I can well imagine that the correct reading is, after all, simply mpra instead of fpra. 
--><!-- 
The punctuation character in l6, if it is one, is a short horizontal dash. 
--></p>
        <p>pākkaṇa-rāṣṭṭre dīrgghadrahaṁ <surplus>n</surplus>nāma grāma<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied><surplus>|</surplus><space/> śailapura-mārgge Asi-bhukti-
<lb n="8"/>mahallamalāṭa-grāmaś ca <space/> evaṁ grāma-dvayaṁ<surplus>||</surplus> pravar<choice>
            <sic>a</sic>
            <corr>e</corr>
